The Sanjuban Shin were established on the premise of a state-protecting concept based on Buddhist teachings as recorded in scriptures such as the Lotus Sutra, the Kanjo Sutra, and {{ill|english|de|german|ja|仁王経|lt=english|lt_ja=仁王般若波羅蜜経|lt_de=german}}, within the development of Shinto-Buddhist syncretism.

Currently, due to the adoption of the {{ill|english|de|german|ja|グレゴリオ暦|lt=english|lt_ja=太陽暦|lt_de=german}}, which includes a 31st day, there are instances where, as the deity for the 31st day, the Five Benevolent Gods ({{ill|english|de|german|ja|薬王菩薩}}, 勇施菩薩, {{ill|english|de|german|ja|多聞天}}, {{ill|english|de|german|ja|持国天}}, {{ill|english|de|german|ja|鬼子母神}}, {{ill|english|de|german|ja|十羅刹女}}) are enshrined.<ref>[http://www.hokkeshu.com/event/dic_sa_30.html 法華宗(陣門流)｜三十番神、三十一日はどうなるの]</ref>

